<div style="background-color:rgba(0,0,0,0.5); padding:5px 10px; text-align:center;"><font size="6">FIN</font></div>
Is this the outcome I once imagined? Have people finally come to understand something? When they gained the ability to do more normal things, did they instead choose stagnation—leading to this moment? Does this signal the arrival of an era built upon stability? Or have they already found somewhere else to belong?

By all reason, I should feel glad—but is such an emotion truly correct?

Nothing I see has changed, and so my feelings remain unchanged. I cannot tell whether this will become an endless abyss, or whether one day everything will simply shut down. Will I live to see that day? Or did it already end the moment it lost its meaning? Is the firmament itself questioning me in some way?

Perhaps it must be admitted: nature was indeed abandoned by humanity, along with many things that should have been taken away. It is not environmentally sound—but they do not care. And gradually, neither do I. Look closely—flowers still bloom, life still grows; perhaps that alone is enough to serve as an explanation.

Then why do I remain here? Is everything I see merely an endlessly prolonged illusion? Is this some form of punishment—opposing my very existence? But I am only trying to understand this phenomenon—is that not within my freedom? Or is it that—you are envious?

No... perhaps not. This form once stood as one of the most mainstream entertainments, and it remains so today, just has experienced periods of decline. Then where did my misunderstanding arise? Was it a single imbalance that sent my thoughts astray? I begin to wonder—does the quantity of output truly relate to its necessity? Should it not have already been buried in history, refusing to return?

Ironically, I once despised it precisely because it was no longer popular. And now—why are none of you here? Why do you not sit with me and watch these abandoned images?

At this very moment, all I possess is solitude. Only things that cannot respond keep me company.

Why didn’t you tell me sooner?

How much longer must I remain here?

Can anyone give me an answer?

